{"cursor":"12987","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{| class=\"toccolours\" border=\"1\" style=\"float: right; clear: right; margin: 0 0\n1em 1em; border-collapse: collapse;\"\n| align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  - Two representations of the\n| organochloride chloroform. - }\n\nAn 'organochloride', 'organochlorine', 'chlorocarbon', 'chlorinated\nhydrocarbon', 'chloroalkane', or 'chlorinated solvent' is an organic compound\ncontaining at least one covalently bonded atom of chlorine. Their wide\nstructural variety and divergent chemical properties lead to a broad range of\nnames and applications. Many derivatives are controversial because of the\neffects of these compounds on the environment and on human and animal health.\n","linknr":366,"url":"Organochloride","recorded":1362506190,"links":28,"instances":[],"pdf":["http://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/toxprofiles/tp106-c1-b.pdf"],"categories":["Organochlorides|"],"headings":["Physical properties","Natural occurrence","Preparation","Reactions","Applications","Toxicity","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Chloroform2.svg/100px-Chloroform2.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Chloroform-3D-vdW.png/100px-Chloroform-3D-vdW.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Lucas_test.png/300px-Lucas_test.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Appel_Reaction_Scheme.png/250px-Appel_Reaction_Scheme.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Chloroform","Organic_compound","Covalent_bond","Chlorine","Water","Methane","Methyl_chloride","Dichloromethane","Chloroform","Carbon_tetrachloride","Alkaloid","Terpene","Amino_acid","Flavonoid","Steroid","Fatty_acid","Polychlorinated_dibenzodiox